From be29291e22b9ab615d4de2c2556392e6ec6bb0bd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 12:37:48 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: skip HAVE_UNIX_LIKE / DATADIR baking on DJGPP
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DJGPP cross from a Linux host inherits CMake UNIX=1, so the existing
IF(UNIX_LIKE) guard fires and bakes a Linux-host absolute path into
the DOS binary as DATADIR. The binary then tries stat()-ing that
host path at runtime, fails to open data/font_1.fnt, and fatal-exits
during graphics init — caught by the Phase 7 prep smoke launch.

Gating on AND NOT DJGPP makes ResourceManager fall through to
SDL_GetBasePath() + "data/", matching how the binary is shipped on
every other portable NXEngine-evo target.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 20 +++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 30e741c..a17af75 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -185,7 +185,25 @@ IF(PLATFORM STREQUAL "pc")
     else()
         add_definitions("-std=c++11")
     endif()
-    IF(UNIX_LIKE)
+    # DJGPP cross from a Linux host inherits CMake's UNIX=1 unless explicitly
+    # cleared, so without this guard the DJGPP build picks up HAVE_UNIX_LIKE
+    # plus a Linux-host CMAKE_INSTALL_FULL_DATADIR baked in as DATADIR. Both
+    # are wrong on DOS:
+    #
+    #   - HAVE_UNIX_LIKE pushes ResourceManager::getPath into the
+    #     "../share/nxengine/data/" relative-to-binary path, which is the FHS
+    #     layout for system-installed Linux binaries — irrelevant on DOS.
+    #
+    #   - DATADIR bakes the build-host's absolute Linux path
+    #     (e.g., /home/<user>/...build/sysroot/share/nxengine/data/) into the
+    #     DOS binary, which obviously can't exist on the target system.
+    #
+    # Dropping both for DJGPP makes ResourceManager fall through to
+    # `getBasePath() + "data/"`, i.e. data/ co-located with DOSKUTSU.EXE.
+    # That matches how Cave Story / NXEngine-evo on every other platform
+    # (Win32 zip, Vita, Switch) ships, and it matches `make install`'s
+    # C:\DOSKUTSU\DATA\ layout on the CF card.
+    IF(UNIX_LIKE AND NOT DJGPP)
         add_definitions(-DHAVE_UNIX_LIKE)
 
         # Use non-portable install, with hard-coded data directory path,
-- 
